item.description: Join our "bird guy" Glenn d'Entremont on a walk in the morning for a chance to encounter some of the pine barrens birds and other nesting species.  We will meet at Headquarter's and carpool over to Cutter Field where there are many breeding feathered friends at this time of year. Rain date will be scheduled for a future date if weather doesn't cooperate. Don't forget the sunscreen and bugspray!
item.how_to_find_us: Look for the headquarter's parking lot
